# Libraries Directory

This directory contains project-specific hardware drivers and reusable libraries.
PlatformIO will compile them to static libraries and link into the executable file.

## Current Libraries

### MAX31865Adapter/
Adapter implementation for the Adafruit MAX31865 RTD sensor board.

**Purpose**: Implements the `ITemperatureSensor` interface for the MAX31865 PT100 
RTD temperature sensor, enabling dependency injection and testability in the 
heating element controller.

**Key Features**:
- PT100 3-wire mode configuration
- Fault detection and clearing
- Calibrated temperature readings using reference resistor

**Usage**:
```cpp
#include <MAX31865Adapter.h>

MAX31865Adapter sensor(CS_PIN);
sensor.begin();
float temp = sensor.readTemperature();
```

**Dependencies**: 
- Adafruit_MAX31865 library (managed via platformio.ini)

## Adding New Libraries

Place each library in its own subdirectory with:
- Header files (`.h`)
- Implementation files (`.cpp`, if needed)
- `library.json` (optional, for metadata and dependencies)

PlatformIO's Library Dependency Finder will automatically discover and 
link libraries referenced in your source files.

**More Information**:
- https://docs.platformio.org/page/librarymanager/ldf.html
- https://docs.platformio.org/page/librarymanager/config.html
